      "body": "I think that the problem warrants a fix in the real code, not in the test. `AddrManImpl::GetAddr_()` would try to overallocate if the caller passes > 100% which is meaningless. It already handles `max_addresses` properly: `nNodes = std::min(nNodes, max_addresses);`. If there are 1000 addresses and the caller asks for 5000, it would clamp it down to 1000.\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>[patch] clamp down the % of addresses, like already done for `max_addresses`</summary>\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git i/src/addrman.cpp w/src/addrman.cpp\r\nindex 43e7b6a32c..9fb092e9af 100644\r\n--- i/src/addrman.cpp\r\n+++ w/src/addrman.cpp\r\n@@ -812,13 +812,13 @@ nid_type AddrManImpl::GetEntry(bool use_tried, size_t bucket, size_t position) c\r\n std::vector<CAddress> AddrManImpl::GetAddr_(size_t max_addresses, size_t max_pct, std::optional<Network> network, const bool filtered) const\r\n {\r\n     AssertLockHeld(cs);\r\n \r\n     size_t nNodes = vRandom.size();\r\n     if (max_pct != 0) {\r\n-        nNodes = max_pct * nNodes / 100;\r\n+        nNodes = std::min(nNodes, max_pct * nNodes / 100);\r\n     }\r\n     if (max_addresses != 0) {\r\n         nNodes = std::min(nNodes, max_addresses);\r\n     }\r\n \r\n     // gather a list of random nodes, skipping those of low quality\r\ndiff --git i/src/test/fuzz/addrman.cpp w/src/test/fuzz/addrman.cpp\r\nindex a7e7f49d9f..ce50e22916 100644\r\n--- i/src/test/fuzz/addrman.cpp\r\n+++ w/src/test/fuzz/addrman.cpp\r\n@@ -169,14 +169,14 @@ FUZZ_TARGET(addrman, .init = initialize_addrman)\r\n     }\r\n     const AddrMan& const_addr_man{addr_man};\r\n     std::optional<Network> network;\r\n     if (fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeBool()) {\r\n         network = fuzzed_data_provider.PickValueInArray(ALL_NETWORKS);\r\n     }\r\n-    auto max_addresses = fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeIntegralInRange<size_t>(0, 4096);\r\n-    auto max_pct = fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeIntegralInRange<size_t>(0, 4096);\r\n+    auto max_addresses = fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeIntegral<size_t>();\r\n+    auto max_pct = fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeIntegral<size_t>();\r\n     auto filtered = fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeBool();\r\n     (void)const_addr_man.GetAddr(max_addresses, max_pct, network, filtered);\r\n \r\n     std::unordered_set<Network> nets;\r\n     for (const auto& net : ALL_NETWORKS) {\r\n         if (fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeBool()) {\r\n```\r\n</details>",
